        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee>&#160;&#160;As <persName>Mr Marcusson</persName> has honored me&#44;<lb/> with the reading of your letter&#44; I wish<lb/> hereby to add&#44; that I am surprised to<lb/> find&#44; that from what you will have perceived<lb/> in my former letter&#44; and which I was<lb/> sorry to find not printed&#44; that the<lb/> words from such sources should have the least effect on any unprejudized mind.<lb/> As far as I have had the opportunity<lb/> to learn <persName>M. M.</persName> character&#44; I am fully<lb/> convinced of the soundness of his princi<lb/>ples on Judaism&#44; and from what I know<lb/> of the other parties I am certain<lb/> that they are liars who could forswear<lb/> for the sake of gain the living God of<lb/> <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; that no reliance can be placed<lb/> on their assertions&#44; and <sic>wherfore</sic> not<lb/> make them ashamed by a <sic>streight</sic><lb/> forward answer by saying we do not<lb/> believe you nor any mean apostate.<lb/> such are the sentiments of yours&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Sir Respectfully in haste</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">L. Jaroslawski</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I will be in <placeName>Phila</placeName> next month.<lb/> at present for answering or publishing any of these matters<lb/> in your paper&#44; I would best submit to your sound senses<lb/> and judgment why have they neglected so long responding&#63;</p>
          
        </body>
